"{\"uid\": \"newsaf.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-04-China-s-Zheng-Qinwen-wins-gold-in-women-s-Olympic-singles-tennis-1vM5X2RREnC-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  China's Zheng Qinwen claimed the gold medal in the women 's Olympic singles tennis tournament on Saturday after defeating Donna Veki\\u00c4\\u0087 of Croatia in the final.  Zheng won the match 6-2, 6-3 at Roland Garros to claim an historic first singles gold medal for China in Olympic tennis.  Zheng had a solid run in Paris only dropping two sets in the entire tournament, and famously defeated reigning French Open champion and pre-tournament favourite Iga \\u00c5\\u009awi\\u00c4\\u0085tek of Poland in the semifinals on Thursday.  Zheng\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s achievement continues to shine a light on her breakthrough year in which she reached her first Grand Slam singles final at the Australian Open in January, and broke into the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s top 10 rankings.  Following Zheng's victory, China now has 16 gold medals at the Olympic Games in Paris, four more than second-placed Australia.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"